text: Josef Jelínek (born 9 January 1941) is a Czech football player. He played for Czechoslovakia, for which he played 10 matches and scored 2 goals."FOTBAL.CZ – Reprezentace A – statistiky". fotbal.cz. He was a participant in the 1962 FIFA World Cup, where Czechoslovakia won the silver medal. In his country he spent his best years playing for Dukla Prague.Hall of Fame Dukla Praha . fkdukla.cz He won the Czechoslovak First League five times with Dukla; and the Czechoslovak Cup for the three times. Jelínek spent five season in the NASL from 1972 – 1976, playing for the New York Cosmos, the Rochester Lancers and the Boston Minutemen respectively."NASL Soccer North American Soccer League Players-Josef Jelinek". nasljerseys.com. He scored the game-winning goal for New York on a penalty kick in the 86th minute of the Cosmos 2–1 victory over St. Louis in the 1972 Championship final."Cosmos defeat Stars to win NASL title".
